-1 BARDS~
A cowled person stops in front of you and appears to give you
a once over. Appearing to nod to itself, the person speaks in
a melodious voice, "So, interested in the Bards are we, and
well you should."

The person pauses for a moment then continues on, "Let me take
a brief second to dispel a misconception or two you might have.
We, Bards, are not minstrels and troubadours desiring to entertain
you or others with song or verse, though with song and verse
we may advise and/or teach. The desire to be somebody's gopher
never crosses our minds. Nor do personal vendettas have a place
outside of the arena or wars."

Looking pleased the person takes a sip from a decanter under its
cloak and continues its dialogue, "So, now that we have dealt with
the misconceptions let me tell you what the Bards are about and what
we do. We are a clan of chroniclers and collectors. What do we
collect? We collect knowledge, stories of past exploits, and tidings
of current events. Why do we collect and chronicle these things,
because if we do not who will. No one will remember the warriors of
old, the battles, the quests, the loves, the defeats, the failures,
the losses and doomed shall we be to repeat the past. To this end,
we have committed ourselves to learn, remember, advise, and teach this
knowledge to others. We do this by traveling the lands far and wide,
listening to every story, investigating the facts of an event, learning
from our peers within Bards, and from applying what we have learned and
give advice and guidance to our peers within and without the clan."

Taking a deep breath and with a sense of sadness in its voice, "But
this path is not for everyone. Who wishes to remember the past mistakes
or the faults of their friends and companions? Who is willing to be
truthful in all things no matter how small or large? Who wishes to
remain impartial when the heart wishes otherwise? If still undaunted
and desire to learn more please contact my associates, and express your
interest."

Turning away the person walks away waving briefly before disappearing 
from sight.
~
-1 FORSAKEN~
What defines an action as good or evil? It is normally
based on the mores and laws of society...and if that
society is evil or corrupt, what then? True combat has
been wasting away, while corruption strikes across the
realm. A guild devoted to balance and the greater
good, Forsaken openly opposes active evil. Formed of
people with their own unique skills and talents,
people work as a unified force, while following their
own passions. By contributing our own unique style of
socializing, management and fighting, everyone will
learn to trust and respect each other, as well as
honing their own style of combat.
~
-1 BLUE ROSE~
Magic, Wonder and Imagination have always been the allure to the Realms of
Redemption. Lately these virtues have fallen by the way, as seen by the current
demise of the Blue Rose. The Rose itself is reflection of the current state of
the Realms. When in the realms are in Chaos the Rose weakens and withers, when
peace and goodwill prevail the Rose prospers and grows.

Of late many have forsaken and overlooked the beauty and life abounding 
here, seeking instead a quick rise to fame and fortune, only to find themselves
frustrated and at odds with life itself.  This weakens the Rose and the well
being of the denizens of Redemption, causing many to continue their search beyond
its borders.

It is the purpose of the Clan of the Blue Rose to bring back and cultivate a
need for the wonder and beauty of the Realms to use magic and imagination to
make the journey in itself an end to the means. As the Keepers of the Rose, the
clan will become one with the land, one with its magic and beauty one with
Redemption. Many wonders abound, under every rock, behind every tree, behind every
door, round every corner. Stop, look and listen and live this magical life to
its fullest!
~
